We display fixed-width-font text-based graphs and tables in noformat windows but our graphs and tables are of a particular fixed height.  The current noformat window fixed height is just slightly smaller than we'd like such that there's a vertical scrollbar present.  Is there some way we can make the noformat window slightly higher to get rid of the vertical scrollbar?  For background and examples, see https://support.atlassian.com/browse/JSP-82756 .

When displaying a moderate number of columns and issues using the Filter Results gadget it fails to render in Firefox after the resulting data reaches a certain size threshold.

If this happens in JIRA after saving a Filter Results Gadget configuration your are bounced back into the configuration view and the changes are not saved.  It is easier to see the problem by adding the gadget to a Confluence page, such as the following:

{noformat}
{gadget:url=http://jiradev.anim.dreamworks.com/rest/gadgets/1.0/g/com.atlassian.jira.gadgets:filter-results-gadget/gadgets/filter-results-gadget.xml|width=auto}filterId=filter-14541&num=200&showActions=true&columnNames=issuetype%7Cpriority%7Cissuekey%7Csummary%7Cresolution%7Cassignee%7Creporter%7Cstatus%7Cupdated%7Clabels&isConfigured=true&refresh=false{gadget}
{noformat}

For some filters, trying to render this page will fail with num > about 60.  For other filters num must be in the low 100s for the gadget to fail.  When the failure happens the gadget shows the spinning spiral progress bar forever and the Firefox Error Console shows "script stack space quota is exhausted" and a link to this line in the Javascript:

{noformat}
}}return{stringify:stringify,parse:function(text){if(/^[\],:{}\s]*$/.test(text.replace(/\\["\\\/b-u]/g,"@").replace(/"[^"\\\n\r]*"|true|false|null|-?\d+(?:\.\d*)?(?:[eE][+\-]?\d+)?/g,"]").replace(/(?:^|:|,)(?:\s*\[)+/g,""))){return eval("("+text+")")
{noformat}

These same gadgets work fine in IE 8 and only have problems in Firefox.  We do not see performance issues in IE 8 with > 100 issues.  We use this functionality extensively with portlets and would like to finally migrate to gadgets, however this is standing in the way of fully migrating off of portlets.

